  <thing id="spUmDeMaEy" name="Dead Man&apos;s Eyes" description="By peering into a dead creature&apos;s eyes, you may see 1 minute/ level preceding the corpse&apos;s death as seen by the dead creature (for example, if the creature died in its sleep there is likely little to see).  You see these events in compressed time, 1 round for every minute of the corpse&apos;s past. A successful DC 15 concentration check gives near-perfect recall of the events; failure indicates fuzzy recall and partial details. A roll of a natural 1 indicates a mangled, inaccurate version of events.\n\nYou may dismiss the spell at any point, but if you witness the creature&apos;s final moment and it was a violent death, you immediately suffer 2d6 points of nonlethal damage from the empathic resonance of the death." compset="Spell" summary="By peering into a dead creature&apos;s eyes, you may see 1 minute/ level preceding the corpse&apos;s death as seen by the dead creature (for example, if the creature died in its sleep there is likely little to see).">
