  <thing id="spUmDoomwa" name="Doomwail" description="You let loose an ear-scourging howl that deafens and paralyzes creatures in its area of effect.  All those caught within the {i}doomwail{/i} must make a Fortitude saving throw. Those who succeed avoid the worst of the effects but are shaken for 2d4 rounds. Those who fail are shaken for 2d4 rounds and roll d% on the following table to determine the individual effect. These effects persist until magically cured.\n\n{b}d% Effect{/b} \n1-50 deafened \n51-75 paralyzed \n76-00 deafened and paralyzed" compset="Spell" summary="You let loose an ear-scourging howl that deafens and paralyzes creatures in its area of effect.">
