  <thing id="spUmChant" name="Chant" description="As long as you chant, you bring special favor upon your allies and bring disfavor to your enemies. You and your allies gain a +1 luck bonus on all attack rolls, saves, and skill checks while your foes suffer a -1 penalty on such rolls.  You must chant in a clear voice. Any interruption in your chanting, such as a failed concentration check, a {i}silence{/i} spell, or your speaking or casting another spell, ends the effect. As an exception to the general rule, the effects of this spell stack with those of a {i}prayer{/i} spell if cast by a cleric of the same deity and alignment during your chanting." compset="Spell" summary="As long as you chant, you bring special favor upon your allies and bring disfavor to your enemies.">
