  <thing id="spUmGanFar" name="Ganest&apos;s Farstrike" description="You create a bolt of flame that flies from your finger to strike any single target within the range of your sight. Your sight may be augmented with {i}eyes of the eagle{/i} or other effects to increase this range, but visual range based on remote viewing such as {i}scrying{/i} or similar effects do not allow the targeting of this spell. The spell deals 1d4 points of fire damage per caster level (maximum 10d4) and has a chance to set anything flammable that it hits on fire. The bolt flies in a parabolic arc that is clearly visible from a distance and can thus be avoided, which is why a successful Reflex save negates all damage.\n\nThis spell can be substituted for {i}fireball{/i} as the 3rd-level domain spell of the Fire domain." compset="Spell" summary="You create a bolt of flame that flies from your finger to strike any single target within the range of your sight.">
