  <thing id="spUmMirSaf" name="Mirror Safe" description="Similar to a {i}bag of holding{/i}, this spell creates an extra-dimensional space beyond the surface of a mirror. The extra-dimensional space is able to hold 100 lb. per caster level. After {i}mirror safe{/i} has been cast, the caster can access the space freely up to one access per two caster levels. During the casting, the caster can set directions that will allow access to the safe and its contents. The &quot;combination&quot; to open the safe can be as simple as a command word or anything as complicated as the conditions needed to fulfill a {i}magic mouth{/i} activation. Each access opens the safe for a period of up to 5 minutes. If the spell runs out of access uses, it ends, and any items remaining within the mirror stay within the extra-dimensional space; the mirror will continue to radiate a faint lingering magical aura. Any caster may recast this spell to gain access to the space once again. \n\nA successful {i}dispel magic{/i} will end the duration of {i}mirror safe{/i}, but the items stored within remain there. {i}Break enchantment{/i}, {i}limited wish{/i}, {i}miracle{/i}, {i}wish{/i}, and {i}mage&apos;s disjunction{/i} will all end the {i}mirror safe{/i}, eject all items within it, and destroy the mirror. A mirror can have only one {i}mirror safe{/i} cast upon it at any given time, and it may link to only one extra-dimensional space at any given time.\n\nLiving matter can be placed within the {i}mirror safe{/i}. Anything inside the {i}mirror safe{/i} can exit the safe freely and leave the extra-dimensional space regardless of whether the {i}mirror safe{/i} is still active or not. If the spell is active, such an exit uses up one access of the {i}mirror safe{/i}. \n\nAny mirror can be used as the focus, but its dimensions limit the size of the items that can be placed within." compset="Spell" summary="Similar to a {i}bag of holding{/i}, this spell creates an extra-dimensional space beyond the surface of a mirror.">
